24/08/2009
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Prime Minister Emil Boc announced on Friday (August 21st) that the government would ask parliament for a vote of confidence on a bill removing taxation on reinvested profit. He says it provides business with a tool to overcome the challenging economic times. Following recent talks with IMF representatives, Boc announced that the measure would be introduced by the beginning of October. (Hotnews.ro, Mediafax - 21/08/09)
